    "description": "Titian's exuberant mythological painting captures the moment Bacchus leaps from his chariot toward the startled Ariadne, who has been abandoned on Naxos by Theseus. The composition explodes with movement and color — Bacchus's billowing crimson cloak, the brilliant ultramarine sky, and the riotous procession of satyrs and maenads create one of the most chromatically daring works of the Renaissance.",
