    "location": "Musée d'Orsay, Paris",
    "description": "Exhibited at the first Impressionist exhibition in 1874, Morisot's tender painting shows her sister Edma watching over her sleeping infant through a translucent curtain. The delicate interplay of whites — the gauze veil, the baby's dress, the pillow — against the dark dress and hair of the mother creates a study in intimacy and maternal devotion. It was the first painting by a woman shown in an Impressionist exhibition.",
